## Best Practices

1. **Naming**: Classes PascalCase, methods/variables camelCase, constants UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
2. **Immutability**: Prefer `final` fields; use records for DTOs (Java 16+)
3. **Null safety**: Use `Optional<T>` instead of returning null
4. **Exceptions**: Checked exceptions for recoverable errors, unchecked for programming errors
5. **Streams**: Use Stream API over imperative loops for collections
6. **Generics**: Type parameters improve reuse and type safety
7. **Interfaces**: Program to interfaces, not implementations

## Common Patterns

### Record (DTO/Value Object) — Java 16+
```java
public record UserDto(Long id, String name, String email) {}
```

### Optional usage
```java
public Optional<User> findById(Long id) {
    return userRepository.findById(id);
}

// Caller
findById(1L)
    .map(User::getName)
    .orElseThrow(() -> new NotFoundException("User not found"));
```

### Stream API
```java
List<String> activeNames = users.stream()
    .filter(User::isActive)
    .map(User::getName)
    .sorted()
    .collect(Collectors.toList());
```

### Builder pattern
```java
User user = User.builder()
    .name("John")
    .email("john@example.com")
    .active(true)
    .build();
```

## Testing

```java
@Test
void shouldReturnUserById() {
    // Arrange
    User expected = new User(1L, "John");
    when(repository.findById(1L)).thenReturn(Optional.of(expected));

    // Act
    User result = service.findById(1L);

    // Assert
    assertThat(result).isEqualTo(expected);
}
```

